00:00:38.131 --> 00:00:40.636
The power rule is very powerful.

00:00:40.636 --> 00:00:43.872
So we can multiply the
1/4th times the coefficient.

00:00:43.872 --> 00:00:47.522
So you have five times 1/4th

00:00:47.522 --> 00:00:51.022
x to the 1/4th minus one power.

00:00:51.985 --> 00:00:54.769
That's the derivative of
five x to the 1/4th power.

00:00:54.769 --> 00:00:56.677
And then we have plus seven.

00:00:56.677 --> 00:00:59.030
Now what's the derivative of seven,

00:00:59.030 --> 00:01:00.527
